### All requests go through the API Gateway (port 5000)
@gateway = http://localhost:5000

### Login
# @name login
POST {{gateway}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test1234!"
}

### Place an order — happy path (any card NOT ending in 0002)
# Saga: OrderCreated -> stock reserved -> payment processed -> Confirmed
POST {{gateway}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "productName": "Sample Product",
      "unitPrice": 109.99,
      "quantity": 2
    }
  ],
  "shippingAddress": "Ataturk Cad. No:1 Istanbul",
  "cardNumber": "4111111111111111"
}

### Place an order — payment failure + compensation (card ending 0002)
# Saga: stock reserved -> payment DECLINED -> stock released -> Cancelled
POST {{gateway}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "productName": "Sample Product",
      "unitPrice": 109.99,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "shippingAddress": "Ataturk Cad. No:1 Istanbul",
  "cardNumber": "4000000000000002"
}

### My orders
GET {{gateway}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Order detail (poll to watch Pending -> Confirmed/Cancelled)
GET {{gateway}}/api/orders/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Stock of a product (Inventory service, via gateway)
GET {{gateway}}/api/inventory/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
